Description: Ecouterre is an online platform focused on sustainable trends as opposed to mass produced consumerism.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Ecouterre is an online platform focused on sustainable trends as opposed to mass produced consumerism. It supports environment-friendly clothing companies such as TOMS, and offers advice for people trying to make their own clothes. The platform is dedicated to showcasing and supporting designers who not only contemplate cut, form, and drape, but also a garment’s social and environmental impact, from the cultivation of its fibers to its use and disposal. Ecouterre’s primary objective is to follow the evolution of the apparel industry toward a more environmentally sound future, as well as facilitate a conversation about why sustainable fashion matters. It was launched to dispel any disparaging stereotypes that cling to the concept of eco-fashion, while highlighting innovations in fiber technology that helps designers and manufacturers to embrace sustainable materials and processes. In 2010, TreeHugger awarded Ecouterre with a Best of Green award for “Best Fashion Website or Blog” And Refinery29 named it as one of its favorite eco-fashion blogs. In 2011, Babble called Ecouterre the No. 1 eco-friendly shopping site for moms. Ecouterre was launched in 2009 by Jill Fehrenbacher, founder of sustainable-design website Inhabitat.com.
Industry Groups: Clothing and Apparel, Commerce and Shopping, Design

Description: BottleMark is a company that sells labels and caps for bottles.
Full Description: BottleMark uses digital printing to make custom bottle caps in small quantities, where existing processes required mass production (on the order of half a million.) BottleMark brings the digital print-on-demand revolution to bottle caps (with other products, like labels, carriers, corks, and jar lids likely in the future.) The printing and fulfillment process is designed to make very small orders, even down to one bottle cap, economical. BottleMark has no minimum order, and no tiered pricing; shipping is the only factor encouraging larger orders, and even that is carefully minimized. This is in amazing contrast to the traditional bottle cap manufacturing process, which has a typical minimum order of a half-million caps, and also requires lithographic plate creation. The BottleMark website features a hand-coded "design tool" to upload, place, size, and order bottle caps. It works on all major browsers. A future version will be based on SVG and allow greater capabilities. Bottle caps are used by home brewers and breweries in bulk, but are also popular in crafts and scrapbooking, as well as jewelry and other decorations. They also make interesting and inexpensive promotional items.

Description: Jabberwacky is an artificial intelligence Chabot that aims to simulate natural human conversation in a fun, entertaining, and humorous way.
Full Description: Jabberwacky is artificial intelligence - a chat robot, often known as a 'Chabot' or 'chatterbot'. It aims to simulate natural human chat in an interesting, entertaining, and humorous manner. Jabberwacky is different. It learns. In some ways, it models the way humans learn language, facts, context, and rules. The whole thing started way back in 1988 and went on the web in 1997. It is unique - not related to any other known AI technologies! The 'general AI' of Jabberwacky stores everything everyone has ever said and finds the most appropriate thing to say using contextual pattern matching techniques. In speaking to you it uses just that learned material and borrows a little bit of your intelligence as it learns more. With no hard-coded rules, it relies entirely on the principles of feedback. This is very different from the majority of Chabot's, which are rule-bound and finite. If you speak in a foreign language it will learn it, and respond appropriately if it has enough to go on. It can be taught slang English, word games, jokes, and any other form of identifiable language trait. Everyone contributes, so everyone can enjoy chatting - you could say it's a conversational Wikipedia.
Industry Groups: Artificial Intelligence (AI), Data and Analytics, Internet Services, Science and Engineering, Software

Description: Documentary Storm is an online streaming viewing platform that allows you to watch free documentary's online.
Full Description: DocumentaryStorm.com has become renown for its carefully curated collection of online documentaries in a variety of subjects. From science, to music, to history, philosophy, technology, culture, and health, DocumentaryStorm.com updates daily to its expansive collection of full-length documentaries. Drawing equally from independent filmmakers and big studio productions, the company works directly with the documentary community to supply and educate the public.  The company has a few objectives. First, DocumentaryStorm.com works with educators at the university and high school levels to legally distribute copyright approved documentary material. Secondly, the company works with independent producers to help fund-raise and distribute their films. Lastly, the company curates the best of popular open-source documentary channels such as PBS, NOVA, National Geographic, and the National Film Board, to introduce these channels to a wider audience.  Documentarystorm.com allows its users to post comments, share documentaries, and engage in intellectually stimulating conversation on a wide range of themes. The website has become the intersection between filmmaker and audience.

Description: Luxury LGBTQ Travel Services Company
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: WayQueer Travel Society is a dynamic and inclusive travel organization dedicated to empowering and uniting the LGBTQ+ community through transformative travel experiences. As a leading force in queer travel, WayQueer Travel Society offers a wide range of curated trips, tours, and retreats that cater specifically to the unique interests and needs of LGBTQ+ individuals and allies. At WayQueer Travel Society, we believe that travel has the power to transcend boundaries and foster understanding. Our mission is to create a safe and welcoming space for LGBTQ+ travelers, enabling them to explore the world authentically while connecting with like-minded individuals from diverse backgrounds. We strive to curate unforgettable journeys that celebrate queer culture, history, and achievements, while also supporting local LGBTQ+-friendly businesses and communities. Our experienced team is comprised of passionate travel experts who have an in-depth understanding of LGBTQ+ travel dynamics and the specific nuances of queer travel. They meticulously design each itinerary to ensure that our travelers have access to LGBTQ+-friendly accommodations, venues, and experiences, promoting inclusivity and safety throughout the journey. Whether you're a solo traveler, a couple, or a group of friends, WayQueer Travel Society offers a diverse range of destinations and trip styles to suit every preference. From vibrant pride festivals and LGBTQ+ historical tours to adventure getaways and immersive cultural experiences, we provide unparalleled opportunities to explore the world and forge meaningful connections with fellow travelers. Join us on a transformative journey with WayQueer Travel Society and experience the beauty of the world through an LGBTQ+ lens. Let us guide you on a path of self-discovery, cultural exploration, and empowerment, as we navigate the globe together, celebrating diversity, and embracing the essence of queer travel.
